verbose_text: Moreover, the concentrations of inflammatory cytokines were measured and the results disclosed that NEAT1 silencing strikingly decreased the levels of tumor necrosis factor (TNF)-alpha, interleukin (IL)-6, IL-8 and IL-beta in LPS induced RAW 264.7 and HL-1 cells (XREF_FIG F, G).
evidence: tumor necrosis factor (TNF)-alpha, interleukin (IL)-6, IL-8 and IL-beta in LPS-induced RAW 264.7 and HL-1
